              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes. Google Tag Manager is free for standard web and app use. Google Tag Manager 360 (enterprise) is a paid tier that adds more workspaces, approvals, and SLA guarantees.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the difference between a tag and a trigger in GTM?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>A tag is the code you want to fire (e.g., GA4 event, Meta Pixel, conversion script). A trigger is the condition that determines when the tag fires (e.g., page view, button click, form submission). Tags fire only when their associated trigger conditions are met.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Can I use Tag Manager without Google Analytics?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Absolutely. GTM is platform-agnostic. You can deploy Hotjar, Segment, HubSpot tracking, LinkedIn Insight Tag, TikTok Pixel, or any custom JavaScript without ever installing Google Analytics.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
